task.summary:
v0.10 "can someone switch trashbot to decaf or something?"
- split BattleBot.java and KaraokeBot.java into a manager and object class. this means that multiple instances of karaoke and battle can be run at the same time. Now, only the person who initiates a battle can send commands to it. - implemented a temporary logger into trashbotBoot.java as a proof of concept. - !add and !remove commands have been implemented into instantHumorContains and instantHumorEquals. - slightly altered the way permissions are loaded into EmojiReactions - new UptimeModule object, which keeps track of trashbot uptime. new !recorduptime command which reports the record of how long trashbot has ran nonstop. - new !devsendmessage command, which sends a message to every server that trashbot is on. - new !panic command, which gracefully kills the bot (although does not stop the process, this needs to be looked into) - trashbot no longer responds to his name in passing, you must @ him. - karaoke should end as soon as the song ends - new !givelyrics command for karaoke, saves a new set of lyrics to the file. requires blue keycard

v0.11 "you can commit if you want to, you can leave your old repo behind" (safety push)
